635
00:49:13,659 --> 00:49:14,826
Are you hurt?

636
00:49:18,622 --> 00:49:21,875
I don't want to talk about today's events.

637
00:49:25,003 --> 00:49:25,962
You're right.

638
00:49:26,588 --> 00:49:27,547
It feels wrong.

639
00:49:30,217 --> 00:49:32,678
Why do we have to drag the students out?

640
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:35,180
It's unfair.

641
00:49:37,891 --> 00:49:39,518
If we say that it's not right,

642
00:49:40,185 --> 00:49:41,478
will something change?

643
00:49:44,064 --> 00:49:45,565
It's not like

644
00:49:45,982 --> 00:49:47,984
I'd give up becoming a cop
after all this hard work.

645
00:49:58,120 --> 00:50:00,038
The students probably got hurt as well.

646
00:50:06,670 --> 00:50:08,380
I'm going to become a police in two days!

647
00:50:10,382 --> 00:50:11,675
Congratulations.

648
00:50:12,008 --> 00:50:13,093
Congrats.

649
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:21,768
Hello.

650
00:50:23,103 --> 00:50:25,313
The chicken
is from the school dean and president.

651
00:50:25,814 --> 00:50:27,607
There are coke and juice,

652
00:50:27,691 --> 00:50:30,569
so enjoy them like they are beer!

653
00:51:23,413 --> 00:51:25,624
-Guys, we're police officers now.
-Yes!

654
00:51:28,710 --> 00:51:30,128
I have a job too!

655
00:51:30,587 --> 00:51:32,172
I'm not a loser anymore!

656
00:51:32,255 --> 00:51:35,675
I'm a police officer now!
A police officer!

657
00:51:36,301 --> 00:51:39,262
Sang-su, receive my salute. Attention!

658
00:51:39,596 --> 00:51:40,889
-As you were.
-As you were!

659
00:52:05,539 --> 00:52:08,834
-Han Jeong-o!
-Han Jeong-o!

660
00:52:11,962 --> 00:52:13,255
Hye-ri, you're up.

661
00:52:15,298 --> 00:52:17,843
Song Hye-ri, Song Hye-ri!

662
00:52:35,068 --> 00:52:37,112
-Hello.
-Good day.

663
00:52:37,654 --> 00:52:39,114
-Good morning.
-Morning.

664
00:52:39,322 --> 00:52:40,699
Hello, everyone.

665
00:52:42,784 --> 00:52:44,202
Are they the rookies?

666
00:52:45,078 --> 00:52:47,080
-Do well today.
-Good day.

667
00:52:58,967 --> 00:52:59,968
-Hello.
-Hi.

668
00:53:00,051 --> 00:53:01,845
Rookies...

669
00:53:05,974 --> 00:53:08,310
This is the men's locker room,
and this is the women's.

670
00:53:08,393 --> 00:53:09,895
Change into your uniforms

671
00:53:09,978 --> 00:53:13,023
and gather outside
the men's locker room in ten minutes.

672
00:53:13,106 --> 00:53:14,274
-Yes, sir.
-Yes.

673
00:53:18,778 --> 00:53:20,113
-Come in.
-Yes, sir.

674
00:53:24,284 --> 00:53:26,661
-So?
-I'm probationary officer Yeom Sang-su.

675
00:53:26,745 --> 00:53:28,955
Do you really have to ask?

676
00:53:29,331 --> 00:53:31,917
I'm telling you I went
all the way to the restaurant.

677
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:33,585
Does he count the number of pieces?

678
00:53:33,668 --> 00:53:37,047
-This is yours. See your name?
-I went with him.

679
00:53:37,339 --> 00:53:39,758
He lined up the drumsticks,
thighs and wings...

680
00:53:39,841 --> 00:53:41,843
-Do I sound condescending?
-He ordered it...

681
00:53:41,927 --> 00:53:44,220
-We're the same age, but I have seniority.
-Yes, sir.

682
00:53:44,304 --> 00:53:46,056
-Change and standby.
-Did he count the pieces?

683
00:53:46,139 --> 00:53:48,058
Of course he did.

684
00:53:48,141 --> 00:53:49,142
It was a perfect set.

685
00:53:49,392 --> 00:53:51,811
Each set had 18 pieces.

686
00:53:51,895 --> 00:53:53,563
The gizzard was cut into four pieces.

687
00:53:54,147 --> 00:53:58,902
That means the owner didn't commit fraud.

688
00:53:59,945 --> 00:54:02,447
-That's crazy.
-It's nothing to laugh about though.

689
00:54:02,530 --> 00:54:04,199
Because of it,

690
00:54:04,282 --> 00:54:06,952
