750
00:56:42,023 --> 00:56:44,818
<i>You're back, welcome back</i>

751
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:47,278
<i>Dear Ms. Sook-ja</i>

752
00:56:47,487 --> 00:56:50,156
You're back as if you made an appointment.

753
00:56:50,240 --> 00:56:54,285
Why did you bring so much with you today?

754
00:56:54,369 --> 00:56:55,787
Who's in charge of the rookies?

755
00:56:55,870 --> 00:56:57,956
Senior Choi, sir.

756
00:56:58,039 --> 00:57:00,542
Your vests are yellow, mine is black.

757
00:57:00,917 --> 00:57:01,960
What's the difference?

758
00:57:02,043 --> 00:57:04,504
He bought his, ours were supplied.

759
00:57:04,587 --> 00:57:06,798
Buy your own off the Internet.

760
00:57:06,881 --> 00:57:09,134
Your pants are straight-leg,
mine are tailored.

761
00:57:09,217 --> 00:57:11,261
Pay to get your pants altered.

762
00:57:11,636 --> 00:57:13,012
My belt is leather.

763
00:57:13,096 --> 00:57:15,098
To look good, buy your own.

764
00:57:17,058 --> 00:57:19,769
Rookies, release your batons.

765
00:57:26,901 --> 00:57:28,695
Put them back.

766
00:57:37,036 --> 00:57:39,747
Mine was imported, yours were supplied.

767
00:57:39,831 --> 00:57:42,417
If you're jealous, buy your own.

768
00:57:47,213 --> 00:57:50,800
We collect 100,000 won a month
for food regardless of rank.

769
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:53,219
Yeom Sang-su,
you will collect it the day after payday.

770
00:57:53,553 --> 00:57:55,930
So 70,000 won is for food,
30,000 is for the team.

771
00:57:56,306 --> 00:57:57,140
Got it.

772
00:57:57,724 --> 00:58:00,226
-What does the team spend it on?
-How would he know?

773
00:58:00,435 --> 00:58:03,188
Coffee, drinks, team dinners
and other things.

774
00:58:03,396 --> 00:58:05,523
The government pays for nothing.

775
00:58:05,607 --> 00:58:08,818
We have one unwritten rule.
You can upset the head of patrol,

776
00:58:09,402 --> 00:58:10,653
but do not upset the cook.

777
00:58:11,696 --> 00:58:14,908
Soy sauce, red pepper paste,
chili powder, salt, various sauces.

778
00:58:15,408 --> 00:58:17,785
Small plates, big plates, pots and pans.

779
00:58:17,869 --> 00:58:19,996
Remember where they're all kept.

780
00:58:20,079 --> 00:58:22,790
-If you don't clean up...
-Your superiors must.

781
00:58:22,874 --> 00:58:24,292
Don't make us do that.

782
00:58:24,375 --> 00:58:25,710
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

783
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:31,382
Memorize all the supplies,

784
00:58:31,466 --> 00:58:34,052
sort them out in the backyard
and go on patrol.

785
00:58:35,011 --> 00:58:36,012
Yes, sir.

786
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:43,269
Did you understand everything they said?

787
00:58:43,353 --> 00:58:44,729
Am I the only who didn't?

788
00:58:44,938 --> 00:58:46,523
You're the only one who didn't.

789
00:58:47,732 --> 00:58:49,901
You should've taught me sooner then.

790
00:58:59,410 --> 00:59:01,746
This house was robbed recently.

791
00:59:01,829 --> 00:59:03,998
And in that alley

792
00:59:04,123 --> 00:59:06,376
someone reported students smoking.

793
00:59:06,501 --> 00:59:07,418
Okay.

794
00:59:07,502 --> 00:59:09,420
-Hello.
-You're hard at work.

795
00:59:09,504 --> 00:59:10,880
Don't catch a cold.

796
00:59:10,964 --> 00:59:13,258
-Take care.
-Thanks.

797
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:17,679
To the right is a dangerous area.

798
00:59:17,762 --> 00:59:20,139
We get three calls a day.

799
00:59:20,473 --> 00:59:23,142
Up to 20 or 30 on Fridays and weekends.

800
00:59:24,102 --> 00:59:26,354
Violence, robbery, stabbings,

801
00:59:26,437 --> 00:59:29,107
fraud, rape, sexual assault,

802
00:59:30,275 --> 00:59:31,317
and more.

803
00:59:34,195 --> 00:59:36,990
Look over there. Damn it.

804
00:59:37,073 --> 00:59:39,200
She's completely drunk.

805
00:59:39,284 --> 00:59:41,995
Hold on. Damn. Stop the car.

806
00:59:43,997 --> 00:59:46,791
Are you crazy?
Probationary Patrol Officers aren't cops.

807
00:59:47,333 --> 00:59:50,253
You can get fired if you're useless, okay?

808
00:59:52,213 --> 00:59:53,214
Get out.

809
01:00:00,847 --> 01:00:02,390
Stand with your hands behind your back.

810
01:00:05,184 --> 01:00:06,185
Ma'am.

811
01:00:07,020 --> 01:00:08,229
Are you all right?

812
01:00:20,617 --> 01:00:21,618
Sir.

813
01:00:22,285 --> 01:00:23,286
Wake up.

814
01:00:23,995 --> 01:00:25,079
Wake up.

815
01:00:26,998 --> 01:00:28,499
Get out, sir.

816
01:00:44,349 --> 01:00:45,308
Leave me alone.

817
01:00:45,391 --> 01:00:46,392
What's wrong?

818
01:00:46,476 --> 01:00:49,896
-What's your problem?
-Come at me.

819
01:00:50,396 --> 01:00:51,981
Sit down, you two.

820
01:00:52,065 --> 01:00:53,191
Sit down!

821
01:00:53,733 --> 01:00:56,903
If you keep fighting, we'll lock you up
for obstruction of justice.

822
01:00:56,986 --> 01:00:58,279
-What a mess.
-Like this?

823
01:00:58,363 --> 01:01:01,032
Yes, sort all that out first.

824
01:01:01,240 --> 01:01:02,575
-I'm a police officer.
-Be careful.

825
01:01:02,659 --> 01:01:04,452
-Be aware of fires.
-I have to move you.

826
01:01:04,535 --> 01:01:06,162
Yeom Sang-su, where are you?

827
01:01:06,371 --> 01:01:07,830
I'm trying to get his ID.

828
01:01:07,914 --> 01:01:09,957
What about the patrol car?
Shouldn't you clean it?

829
01:01:10,041 --> 01:01:12,251
-I'll clean it right away.
-Move, move.

830
01:01:12,335 --> 01:01:14,128
-Hey...
-Let me borrow this before I get fired.

831
01:01:14,212 --> 01:01:17,173
Hey. I really need help.

832
01:01:17,256 --> 01:01:19,676
Here, I can't help you, so listen.

833
01:01:20,134 --> 01:01:23,513
Are you going to quit
before probation's over?

834
01:01:24,263 --> 01:01:25,556
Use your hands.

835
01:01:40,113 --> 01:01:41,614
That hurts.

836
01:01:42,532 --> 01:01:45,243
What's going on? What happened?

837
01:01:48,371 --> 01:01:49,831
Hey, are you sleeping?

838
01:01:50,456 --> 01:01:54,585
Are you expecting special treatment
because you're a woman?

839
01:01:54,669 --> 01:01:55,962
No, sir.

840
01:01:59,006 --> 01:02:00,466
Do you feel better, sir?

841
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:03,010
Oh dear, try to get up.

842
01:02:03,094 --> 01:02:04,470
Be careful.

843
01:02:07,306 --> 01:02:09,726
Unclog it. Okay?

844
01:03:22,298 --> 01:03:26,719
NIGHTTIME CIVIL AFFAIRS SERVICE

845
01:03:38,189 --> 01:03:40,358
You're really lucky.

846
01:03:40,608 --> 01:03:41,651
When I was a rookie,

847
01:03:42,318 --> 01:03:45,112
I had to deal with stabbings all the time.

848
01:03:47,031 --> 01:03:50,576
All you have to deal with are drunks.

849
01:03:51,452 --> 01:03:53,496
You're really fortunate.

850
01:03:55,581 --> 01:03:56,958
Hallelujah.

851
01:04:02,380 --> 01:04:04,590
Instant noodles should be
regulated by law.

852
01:04:05,299 --> 01:04:07,426
All these instant noodles... Gosh.

853
01:04:08,177 --> 01:04:11,472
Did I go through all that crap
to become a cop to do this?

854
01:04:13,057 --> 01:04:15,685
I want to get involved in a real case.

855
01:04:16,435 --> 01:04:18,104
Like a theft or a murder.

856
01:05:10,489 --> 01:05:12,116
I'm off to school.

857
01:05:45,524 --> 01:05:47,485
Hey! Wake up!

858
01:05:52,323 --> 01:05:53,366
Wake up.

859
01:05:53,449 --> 01:05:54,408
What now?

860
01:05:55,409 --> 01:05:57,161
Are you kidding me?

861
01:06:00,247 --> 01:06:01,499
Is this why you took time off?

862
01:06:01,874 --> 01:06:02,875
You brat.

863
01:06:04,752 --> 01:06:08,130
<i>The number you have dialed
is not available. Please leave a...</i>

864
01:06:14,512 --> 01:06:16,555
Ho-cheol's wife won't answer her phone.

865
01:06:18,641 --> 01:06:21,686
She must believe that
I actually caused his death.

866
01:06:28,275 --> 01:06:29,402
Are you going to work today?

867
01:06:30,695 --> 01:06:31,737
To the station?

868
01:06:32,905 --> 01:06:34,657
Why the Women & Juvenile Affairs Division?

869
01:06:35,324 --> 01:06:37,201
You transferred out two years ago.

870
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:39,412
Why not another division?

871
01:06:46,293 --> 01:06:48,254
Why won't you talk to me?

872
01:06:48,713 --> 01:06:50,172
I'm your husband.

873
01:06:56,554 --> 01:06:58,264
Why did Song-yi take time off school?

874
01:06:58,681 --> 01:07:00,266
She should graduate and get married.

875
01:07:01,475 --> 01:07:02,476
What's her plan?

876
01:07:06,188 --> 01:07:07,231
Huh?

877
01:07:08,441 --> 01:07:09,483
Let's get a divorce.

878
01:07:17,950 --> 01:07:20,995
Didn't you hear me? I want a divorce.

879
01:07:41,432 --> 01:07:42,516
-Are you done?
-Thank you.

880
01:07:42,600 --> 01:07:43,768
-Did you go on patrol?
-Yes.

881
01:07:44,518 --> 01:07:45,603
I'm starving.

882
01:07:59,533 --> 01:08:01,327
Oh Yang-chon is coming to our
Patrol Division.

883
01:08:01,577 --> 01:08:04,246
We should brace ourselves.
It's the chief's direct order.

884
01:08:05,372 --> 01:08:06,707
I feel bad for you.

885
01:08:13,881 --> 01:08:17,468
Gyeong-mo will try and rip his throat out.

886
01:08:18,886 --> 01:08:20,304
Yang-chon won't let it happen.

887
01:08:26,310 --> 01:08:29,230
Are you guys still living in a study room?

888
01:08:29,313 --> 01:08:31,440
-Yes, we couldn't find a place.
-Yes, sir.

889
01:08:31,899 --> 01:08:33,442
There are a few in my neighborhood.

890
01:08:35,402 --> 01:08:36,570
Hey, there.

891
01:08:36,654 --> 01:08:37,655
ZIGBANG

892
01:08:41,408 --> 01:08:42,535
What about this place?

893
01:08:44,328 --> 01:08:45,538
It's quite spacious.

894
01:08:46,038 --> 01:08:47,456
-We could fit a couch.
-Right.

895
01:08:47,540 --> 01:08:48,749
Check it out on your day off.

896
01:08:50,876 --> 01:08:54,088
You've been with us for a week now.

897
01:08:54,171 --> 01:08:57,049
-How do you feel?
-They'll probably feel like dying.

898
01:08:58,592 --> 01:09:02,263
Really? Will you be quitting then?

899
01:09:02,346 --> 01:09:03,639
Go ahead.

900
01:09:03,806 --> 01:09:04,807
No, sir.

901
01:09:06,100 --> 01:09:07,434
What about you?

902
01:09:08,978 --> 01:09:10,396
I want a real task.

903
01:09:11,647 --> 01:09:13,482
I want to solve a big case.

904
01:09:13,858 --> 01:09:14,692
Like a violent crime.

905
01:09:32,710 --> 01:09:35,045
For a week,
I've been wiping puke off drunks,

906
01:09:36,130 --> 01:09:38,174
helping old ladies with dementia get home,

907
01:09:39,133 --> 01:09:41,093
and going out on traffic control.

908
01:09:50,102 --> 01:09:53,898
We're just saying that
we want to do real police work.

909
01:09:54,899 --> 01:09:57,818
We're the police,
but we practically do nothing

910
01:09:57,902 --> 01:09:59,695
while living off the people's tax money.

911
01:09:59,778 --> 01:10:01,363
As civil servants,

912
01:10:01,447 --> 01:10:03,240
we feel guilty for...

913
01:10:03,324 --> 01:10:06,035
<i>Code zero. 765 Imhyeon Intersection.</i>

914
01:10:06,118 --> 01:10:08,621
<i>A sexual assault has been reported.</i>

915
01:10:08,704 --> 01:10:09,955
<i>Code zero.</i>

916
01:10:10,456 --> 01:10:13,542
-<i>Code zero. 765 Imhyeon Intersection.</i>
-Are you kidding me?

917
01:10:13,626 --> 01:10:16,795
<i>A sexual assault has been reported.</i>

918
01:10:17,463 --> 01:10:19,173
Are you happy now?

919
01:10:19,673 --> 01:10:22,218
We were assigned a violent crime
thanks to your big mouth.

920
01:10:22,301 --> 01:10:25,054
There's a jinx. The moment someone's says

921
01:10:25,137 --> 01:10:28,182
we're not doing real police work,
we'll get thrown a messy one.

922
01:10:28,265 --> 01:10:29,391
You and your big mouth!

923
01:10:29,475 --> 01:10:32,561
<i>Code zero. 765 Imhyeon Intersection.</i>

924
01:10:32,645 --> 01:10:35,689
<i>A sexual assault has been reported.</i>

925
01:10:37,358 --> 01:10:39,902
The last rookie to hop on the squad car

926
01:10:39,985 --> 01:10:41,570
is dead meat! Run!

927
01:11:30,244 --> 01:11:31,453
<i>What are you looking at?</i>

928
01:11:31,537 --> 01:11:33,914
<i>-We'll stay safe today.
-We'll stay safe today.</i>

929
01:11:33,998 --> 01:11:35,499
A patrol division? Sounds good.

930
01:11:35,582 --> 01:11:36,667
I hear he's a total legend.

931
01:11:37,251 --> 01:11:39,003
-Stop!
-What's his name?

932
01:11:40,921 --> 01:11:42,089
-Oh Yang-chon.
-Damn.

933
01:11:42,423 --> 01:11:44,842
<i>Stop making your hatred for him obvious.
You'll get fired.</i>

934
01:11:45,509 --> 01:11:48,012
You can't assault your juniors
in this day and age!

935
01:11:48,095 --> 01:11:50,097
Yang-chon,
did you write your letter of resignation?

936
01:11:50,723 --> 01:11:52,850
-<i>Han Jeong-o seems nice.</i>
-I'll work harder

937
01:11:54,101 --> 01:11:58,647
so that this never happens again.
I honestly don't know what I did wrong.

